    "fact": "Kage's built-in generic-static indexer should not stop at symbols and imports for non-TypeScript code. It now extracts bounded call edges for supported generic languages and marks generic test functions as test symbols, so Python/Go/Rust/Ruby/PHP/Java/Kotlin/C#/C++/Swift repos get more useful call/test graph signals even without SCIP, LSP, or tree-sitter artifacts."
